 class="cols_2 cl relative">                <div class="col_1">                    <h1>Website Grants</h1>                    <div id="ContentPlaceHolder_Main_CMS_Content" class="content">	                                                    <div>\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Website Grants</h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>The Closing Date for Receipt of Website Grant Applications is Wednesday 12th March 2014</strong><span>.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Subject to funding, the grant available may be offered at a rate of up to 50% of the eligible cost of your website.  A maximum of €1,000 is available for websites with a sell on-line facility and for those developing or upgrading a brochure website, a maximum of 50% of the cost up to a maximum of €500 is available. </p>\n<h4 style="text-align: justify;"><span>The following criteria will apply:</span></h4>\n<ol>\n<li><span>Businesses that have been approved for grant aid will have 3 months from the date of approval to drawdown their website grant. Websites not completed and paid for within that period will not be eligible for grant payment.</span></li>\n<li><span>Requests for grant aid must be accompanied by a quotation and proposal from a registered business and completed application form. (Available from Local Enterprise Office Westmeath)</span></li>\n<li><span>Applications will only be accepted from registered businesses in Westmeath employing less than 10 people.</span></li>\n<li><span>A minimum spend on €800 net of VAT is required.</span></li>\n<li><span>The business must have sufficient capacity to warrant a website.</span></li>\n<li><span>All works must be carried out by a registered website provider.</span></li>\n<li><span>Work must not have commenced on the website prior to application being approved.     </span></li>\n</ol>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In the case of businesses who wish to upgrade their website, application must be accompanied by a hardcopy of their current website.</p>\n<h4 style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span>Payment will be made on receipt of:</span></strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Hard copy of Website and showing Westmeath Local Enterprise Office Tagline</span></li>\n<li><span>Proof of payment through bank account to Web Provider</span></li>\n<li><span>Copy of Invoice from the Web Provider</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Please note all websites funded must contain an acknowledgement to Local Enterprise Office Westmeath and include relevant logos which are available to download below</p>\n<ul>\n<li><div style="text-align: justify;"><a href="https://www.localenterprise.ie/Westmeath/Financial-Supports/Other-Financial-Supports/Website%20Grants/LEO_Master_Pos.jpg">LEO_Master_Pos.jpg (size 601 KB)</a></div></li>\n<li><div style="text-align: justify;"><a href="https://www.localenterprise.ie/Westmeath/Financial-Supports/Other-Financial-Supports/Website%20Grants/ERDF.jpg">ERDF.jpg (size 608.8 KB)</a></div></li>\n<li><div style="text-align: justify;">Wording for acknowledgement "this website is part-funded by the Locel Enterprise Office Westmeath" or something similar.</div></li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\n</div>                                                                                                      <div id="map" style="display: none; position: relative; width: 500px; height: 400px;"></div>\n<div id="message" style="display: none;"></div>                                            </div>                </div>                <div class="col_2 last">                    <div class="aside_nav">  <p class="first_level"><a href="https://www.localenterprise.ie/Westmeath/Financial-Supports/">Financial Supports</a><span> </span></p>  <ul>\n<li class=""><a href="https://www.localenterprise.ie/Westmeath/Financial-Supports/Eligibility-Criteria/">Eligibility Criteria</a></li>    <li class=""><a href="https://www.localenterprise.ie/Westmeath/Financial-Supports/Priming-Grant/">Pri